    • Method Detail

      • openMap

        void openMap(UniqueMapInterface map)
        Open a Map and give it a unique ID.

      • setDefaultMap

        void setDefaultMap(UniqueIDInterface map)
        Set the identified Map as the default Map to be used. This is set for some calls or external tools that may not always specify which Map to use. They expect the "current" or "default" Map to be referenced.

      • getDefaultMap

        UniqueIDInterface getDefaultMap()
        Get the ID of the current default map.

      • setDefaultMapSection

        void setDefaultMapSection(UniqueSectionInterface section)
        Set the identified Map Section as the default Section to be used when normal lookups fail. "ApplicationConstants" is the pre-programmed default. This allows us to change that.

      • getDefaultMapSection

        UniqueSectionInterface getDefaultMapSection()
        Get the ID of the current default map section.

      • getMapItem

        java.lang.String getMapItem(UniqueItemInterface item)
        Get the value of a Mapped item.
